added.title: Halloween vs. Christmas
added.description: When Santa tries to take over Halloween, it's up to the Titans and a few ghouls to stop him.

added.title: Teen Titans Save Christmas
added.description: Santa calls it quits so the Titans must pitch in to save the holiday.

added.title: Christmas Crusaders
added.description: Santa Claus and Robin must stop the nefarious Coal Miner.

added.title: How's This for a Special? Spaaaace Part 1
added.description: After receiving a galactic crime alert, the Titans take off for an epic space adventure.

added.title: How's This for a Special? Spaaaace Part 2
added.description: The Titans have to stop Darkseid's latest scheme, but the excitement of the space adventure might be too much for Robin to handle.

added.title: Flashback Part 1
added.description: A flashback reveals how Robin formed the Teen Titans.

added.title: Flashback Part 2
added.description: A flashback reveals how Robin changed from mild-mannered sidekick to quick-tempered leader.

added.title: Mo' Money Mo' Problems
added.description: The Titans make Robin give them a tour of Wayne Manor and discover how fun it is to be rich.

added.title: The Return of Slade
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg insist on hiring a clown for a Titans party, even though Robin tells them that clowns are for little kids. When the clown fails to live up to their memories, Cyborg and Beast Boy decide to give the clown some cool updates.

added.title: Christmas Parties
added.description: The Bears have been invited to all their friends' Christmas parties. In an effort to have time to crash Nom Nom's huge star-studded bash, the Bears first try to make quick stops at all their friends' parties throughout the night.

added.title: The Perfect Tree
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear drive up north to find the perfect Christmas tree. Meanwhile, Grizz and Panda are in charge of decorating Chloe's house.

added.title: Christmas Movies
added.description: On Christmas Eve, the Baby Bears defend a video store from getting robbed.

added.title: Hot Sauce
added.description: A quest for their favorite hot sauce causes the Bears to get involved with a sting operation.

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: Paperboyz
added.description: The Baby Bears get jobs as paper boys.

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: Emergency
added.description: When Grizz comes home with a live crab, he thinks it can become a pet for the brothers to share. However, after the crab pinches Ice Bear's ear and won't let go, Panda and Grizz have to get their injured brother to the hospital, and fast!

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Christmas
added.description: Santa Claus is coming to town. Unfortunately he gets run over by the Wattersons, so it's up to them to save Christmas.

added.title: The Silence
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin's conversation dries up, they worry that their friendship is coming to an end. They try to find ways to get the conversation flowing again, but nothing seems to work. Maybe they have just grown apart?

added.title: The Wish
added.description: Gumball and Darwin panic when they suspect they've accidentally turned Miss Simian into a cushion, by wishing upon an enchanted key ring. Surely the only way to break the curse is a confession of true love from Principal Brown. Simple!

added.title: The Agent
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's clothes go missing after a swimming lesson and Gumball is forced to wear a tuxedo from the lost and found office. He believes it makes him look like a certain dapper British secret agent and, together with Darwin and Bobert (and far too many wisecracks) Gumball track down the villain responsible for stealing his clothes.

added.title: The Mess
added.description: The boys stay up all night, even though the next day they're supposed to be babysitting Polly, Penny's little sister. They're so tired that they manage to lose Polly in the blink of an eye. They desperately look for her, but find themselves in increasingly weird situations every time they accidentally nod off.

added.title: The Revolt
added.description: Darwin tries to highlight the plight of all the household objects he feels are being oppressed and maltreated by the uncaring residents of Elmore. He then decides to lead those objects in a revolt against the townspeople.

added.title: The BFFS
added.description: Gumball's old BFF Fuzzy, turns up on his doorstep. Darwin struggles to accept that there was someone before him and fails to contain his jealousy. But is Darwin right to mistrust Fuzzy? Does Fuzzy actually have sinister motives for reconnecting with his old BFF?

added.title: The Photo
added.description: It's school picture day and Gumball has until 3pm to take one good photo - or have his legacy ruined forever.

added.title: The Boombox
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to understand Juke's urgent Beatbox message, but why won't he just speak English?!!

added.title: Omni-Copped
added.description: When Grandpa Max's engineer buddy Phil Billings gifts Team Tennyson the Omni-Copter, a state of the art flying vehicle that can transport the Rustbucket for overseas adventures, Steam Smythe takes to the skies to ground Ben and company's first test flight; but unbeknownst to our heroes, Smythe was sent to battle Ben's latest alien forms by a mysterious, powerful enemy: the Forever Knight.

added.title: This One Goes to 11
added.description: During one last stop by a toy store before Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max's maiden voyage across the Atlantic, Ben runs into an old bully, Kevin 11, who now has new powers. He's able to transform into aliens just like Ben, such as the bootleg doppelganger of Cannonbolt. Wreckingbolt!

added.title: Rath of Con
added.description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.

added.title: Poles Apart
added.description: A trip to the South Pole goes upside down when Team Tennyson lands on the North Pole instead, but Ben quickly discovers the culprits: Solar & Polar Twain, magnetically-powered scientists who want to hold the world ransom by threatening to reverse Earth's magnetic poles!

added.title: Show Don't Tell
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max arrive at a Native American national park to witness the Ayasha Plinths, an ancient Stonehenge-like rock formation. But when the sinister sorcerer Hex arrives, Ben must battle against a beast Hex magically made out of huge rocks!

added.title: Rustbucket RIP
added.description: During a tour of historic Oldeville Ben finds a rare Sumo Slammers card, but when Billy Billions comes to claim the same card Ben has to battle Billy's high-tech drones which have hijacked the Rust Bucket!

added.title: Freaky Gwen Ben
added.description: When Ben interferes with malicious magician Hex's quest for the earth-moving Titan Gloves at a swap meet, he inadvertently switches bodies with Gwen forcing him to walk a mile in her shoes and vice-versa!

added.title: Ben 24hrs
added.description: When Ben (and Gwen!) attempt to stay up all night for Adrenaland, the only theme park open 24/7, he not only fails to utilize his alien powers to stay awake, but his "sleep-alien-ing" causes disaster after disaster that Gwen must fix before things get way out of hand.

added.title: Bright Lights, Black Hearts
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max stop by the graveyard set of Gwen's favorite TV show, The Unalivers, but when Ben discovers its lead, Michael Morningstar, is an energy vampire he goes alien to show the world the real star of the show: Heatblast.

added.title: Don't Laze Me, Bro
added.description: Ben and his arch-enemy Billy Billions clash in a duel for supremacy at the world's largest Laser Tag Park, LASER TOWN. But, when Billy inadvertently ignites a robot rebellion, and the lasers are set from tag to disintegrate, their childish game escalates into a full blown war! The two foes find that they must set aside their petty differences and team up in order to make it out alive, let alone save the day!

added.title: Summer Wish
added.description: When Craig decides to keep a lightning bug in a jar, he disrupts the delicate balance of Summer.

added.title: Turning the Tables
added.description: Craig dines at the restaurant where his older brother works and orders up a plate of REVENGE... and lots of breadsticks.

added.title: Kelsey the Author
added.description: Craig and Stacks help Kelsey become a real author turning her story into a book!

added.title: Council of the Creek
added.description: The circle game wreaks havoc on the Creek, so Craig forms a council to restore order.

added.title: Sparkle Cadet
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP team up with an intergalactic hero named Sparkle Cadet, hoping to save the Creek from negativity.

added.title: Craig and the Kid's Table
added.description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: Dinner at the Creek
added.description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: Bug City
added.description: Craig discovers a bunch of bugs under a rock and decides to build them a city.

added.title: Deep Creek Salvage
added.description: The Trio finds gold in the muddy depths of the Creek so Craig builds a rig to recover it.

added.title: The Shortcut
added.description: An unusually hot day at the Creek melts all of Kit's ice pops, so Craig helps her find a short cut to her frozen snack supplier before everyone else melts.

added.title: Dibs Court
added.description: When a kid claims dibs on the Stump, Craig has no choice but to take them to court. Dibs Court.

added.title: The Great Fossil Rush
added.description: JP finds a fossil in the Creek which quickly causes the landscape to change.

added.title: The Mystery of the Timekeeper
added.description: When the Time Keeper goes missing, Craig and his friends take up the task of helping kids get home in time for dinner.

added.title: Alone Quest
added.description: Craig has an "emergency" leaving Kelsey alone at the Stump.

added.title: Three Gems and a Baby
added.description: Greg tells Steven the story of his first winter with Steven.

added.title: Winter Forecast
added.description: Steven has to get Connie home before it snows.

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Top of the Naughty List
added.description: It's Christmas Eve and Brock is excited for Santa to come and visit as he settles down for a bedtime story from Master Frown, Unikitty and gang burst in. They are there to stop Master Frown from ruining any more Christmases. Frown pleads innocent but Unikitty and the gang tell the stories of the past Christmases he has already ruined.  Will Frown prove his innocence or will he rocket to the top of the Naughty List?

added.title: Christmas in Space
added.description: The guys celebrate their first Christmas in space by opening presents, eating peppermint bark and telling Christmas stories. Benson wants the stories to be more Christmas-y but the guys keep adding scary elements, which only infuriate their boss.

added.title: Snow Tubing
added.description: Rigby wants Eileen to go snow tubing.

added.title: White Elephant Gift Exchange
added.description: The park guys want revenge on Muscle Man for all his terrible gifts.

added.title: Merry Christmas Mordecai
added.description: Mordecai has to get through a Christmas party with C.J. without messing everything up.

added.title: New Year's Kiss
added.description: Rigby has to stop Mordecai from kissing a girl on New Year's Eve.

added.title: The Christmas Special
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to destroy a gift for Santa to save Christmas.

added.title: Chadsgiving
added.description: Clarence is excited for Thanksgiving Dinner with Chad's parents, but Chad is worried that their unusually laid back demeanor and bizarre customs will make him look irresponsible by association.

added.title: Merry Moochmas
added.description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

added.title: The Gift
added.description: The girls must replace the Professor's Christmas present on Christmas Eve.

added.title: You're a Good Man, Mojo Jojo
added.description: The holidays are Mojo's favorite time…for ruining everything! But this year, he may just learn the reason for the season.

added.title: Snow Month
added.description: After a snow day saves Blossom from having to face a boy who's asked her out, she decides to use her ice breath to keep it going even if that means plunging Townsville into eternal winter complete with monstrous yetis!

added.title: 'Twas the Fight Before Christmas
added.description: When Princess Morbucks tries to ruin Christmas for the children of the world, the Powerpuff Girls must save the day.

added.title: The More You Moe, the Moe You Know
added.description: Moe visits the tree house with a special birthday surprise for BMO. While BMO's mission stands on the brink of disaster, Finn & Jake host a strange guest.

added.title: Holly Jolly Secrets Part 1
added.description: Finn and Jake continue to explore the world of old Christmas specials while the Ice King fumes.

added.title: Holly Jolly Secrets Part 2
added.description: Finn and Jake continue to explore the world of old Christmas specials while the Ice King fumes.

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: Secret Santa
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and the crew all have the same popular and hard-to-find gift in mine for their Secret Santa, their nice Christmas shopping trip to the mall turns into a crazy competition.

added.title: UG Christmas Special
added.description: Santa and Uncle Grandpa must work through their personal differences order to save Christmas.

added.title: Party Animal
added.description: Green Arrow, who is determined to finally throw a successful holiday party for the Justice League, finds his plans thwarted when Plastic Man brings a tranquilized super villain to the gathering.

added.title: Merry Christmas
added.description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple needs to acquire a lifetime supply of toilet paper to finish his modern art sculpture.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple has to find a way not to lose his best friend.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Apple tries to survive a weekend alone while taking care of Onion's plant.

added.title: Party Popper
added.description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears while trapped in a pet shop, so they can save French Fry from facing hers.

added.title: The Fly
added.description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

added.title: Dragonhead
added.description: Apple and Onion must run a secret parking lot on their roof terrace so they can have a shower.

added.title: Pulling Your Weight
added.description: Apple and Onion join a gym to gain the strength of seven people.

added.title: The Inbetween
added.description: Apple and Onion get lost beneath their floorboards and must find a way out.

added.title: Election Day
added.description: Apple runs for Mayor.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: The ninja are invited to attend the birthday party of Princess Vania, in the distant Kingdom of Shintaro. They depart, bringing along Master Wu, unaware that he is feeling his age…

added.title: Into the Dark
added.description: When Cole investigates a mysterious visitor, the ninja aren't sure what to believe. Cole is frustrated with this lack of team support, until Princess Vania reveals a secret entrance that leads to an underground mine beneath Shintaro - where the city's dark secrets are held.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Two Blades
added.description: In order to escape the Skull Sorcerer's chain-gang, the ninja must convince the Munce and Geckles to put aside their distrust and work together… by promising them something they may not be able to deliver -- The Blades of Deliverance!

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: The Guest
added.description: Vic & Val blame each other for eating all the food in the kitchen and making a huge mess! However, they soon discover that a ghost is actually to blame! They enlist the help of Achi to unlock the world of spirits among them and kick the ghost out of their house!

added.title: Ener-G-Shoes
added.description: When Vic uses trickery to buy a pair of super cool sneakers from Maria Teresa's yard sale, the shoes try to walk him to his demise as punishment.

added.title: La Cucarachita
added.description: When Vic's beloved pet cockroach dies, Vic turns to Charlene's dark magic to bring her back to life.

added.title: Lords of Ghost Town
added.description: When V&V recruit a ghost to scare away a bully, they end up messing with the realm of the dead, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: My Fair Achi
added.description: V&V enter Achi in a dog show competition to win a golden trophy, but their overbearing ways drive Achi to the edge.

added.title: Folk Art Foes
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes the lord of mischief from an ancient relic, V and V have to work together to trap it back inside.

added.title: Dead Ringer
added.description: When Vic doesn't pick Val for his soccer team, Val vows to win with his own squad. But when his team doesn't match up, he resorts to supernatural means to win.

added.title: Brotherly Love
added.description: After breaking Chata's plant, Vic and Val must accomplish the seemingly easy task of replacing it; this proves difficult when their squabbling puts Monte Macabre in jeopardy.

added.title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
added.description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

added.title: Legend of the Hidden Skate Park
added.description: While searching for a hidden skate park, V and V happen upon a tribe of wild kids, who live in a society without rules or adults.

added.title: Cleaning Day
added.description: Victor & Valentino gain a newfound respect for cleanliness after Chata's house traps them inside its labyrinth of ancient, magical walls.

added.title: The Babysitter
added.description: Vic & Val want to sneak out to a secret fireworks show but are thwarted when their new babysitter, Xochi, outsmarts them at every turn.

added.title: Hurricane Chata
added.description: When V & V discover that Chata's emotions control the water in the lake, they use it to their advantage and start their own wave pool business.

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club
added.description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

added.title: Suerte
added.description: When Vic cheats on an enchanted board game, the malevolent characters come to life, and it's up to V & V to figure out how to put them back in the game.

added.title: Ratar-O
added.description: The ThunderCats have gotten so good at defeating the Mutants of Plun-Darr that it's basically become routine. That all changes with the arrival of the Mutants' old leader: Ratar-O, wielder of the Sword of Plun-Darr! Uh-oh!

added.title: Prince Starling's Quest
added.description: Lion-O is happily playing with Snarf in their "Frolicking Field" and doesn't have a care in the world, unfortunately he's accidentally stomping all over the miniature village of the Micrits! The tiny people want to defeat the "giant orange monster" but such a quest would require a brave hero. Luckily, the Micrits have such a hero: Prince Starling! Now, let us the tell you the epic tale of Prince Starling as he journeys to find the fountain of growth and defeat the wicked Lion-O, who has no idea any of this is going on!

added.title: Steven's Birthday
added.description: Steven has a birthday party out at the barn, and decides he has some growing up to do.

added.title: It Could've Been Great
added.description: The Gems take a trip to the moon.

added.title: Message Received
added.description: Steven has doubts about believing in everyone.

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Rising Tides, Crashing Skies
added.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Open Book
added.description: Steven and Connie want a new ending to a beloved book series, so Steven takes them into Rose's Room to re-enact it.

added.title: Joy Ride
added.description: The Cool Kids help Steven put some fun back in his life.

added.title: Weapon of Choice
added.description: Worried that his sword is a glorified consolation prize, Mao Mao sets out to prove the worth of his weapon.

added.title: The Truth Stinks
added.description: Badgerclops smells, but Mao Mao and Adorabat don't know how to tell him.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: When they think each others' lives are easier, the heroes switch roles.

added.title: Head Chef
added.description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.

added.title: Orangusnake Begins
added.description: Mao Mao goads Orangusnake and the Sky Pirates into becoming truly terrible villains worthy of a legendary hero such as himself.

added.title: Sugar Berry Fever
added.description: Mao Mao tries to hide his love of cobbler.

added.title: Captured Clops
added.description: Badgerclops is tired of his responsibilities at Sheriff's HQ, so he joins the Sky Pirates.

added.title: Flyaway
added.description: When Adorabat's spirit transcends her body during a meditation exercise, Mao Mao and Badgerclops have to figure out a way to return her to the real world.

added.title: Mao Mao's Nakey
added.description: When MM loses his clothes while trying to scale the Ruby Pure Heart, he has to get back to Sheriff's HQ by daybreak.

added.title: Adoradad
added.description: When AD's dad forbids her from working with the Sheriff's Dept because it's too dangerous, AD sets out to prove that she can take care of herself.

added.title: Bonnibel Bubblegum
added.description: A long lost artifact causes Princess Bubblegum to harken back to the creation of the Candy Kingdom.

added.title: Elements Part 1: Skyhooks
added.description: Upon returning to Ooo, Finn and Jake discover that there have been some radical changes in their absence.

added.title: Elements Part 2: Bespoken For
added.description: Ice King weaves a tale filled with drama, romance, and men's fashion.

added.title: Elements Part 3: Winter Light
added.description: Finn, Jake, and Ice King travel to the new Ice Kingdom to confront the person responsible for turning everything topsy-turvy.

added.title: Islands Part 1: The Invitation
added.description: A mysterious craft invades Ooo and Finn believes it may hold the secrets to his past.

added.title: Islands Part 2: Whipple the Happy Dragon
added.description: Finn, Jake, and Susan set sail on a ocean voyage full of wonders and danger.

added.title: Islands Part 3: Mysterious Island
added.description: After waking up alone and shipwrecked, Finn investigates a bizarre island in search of his friends.

added.title: Grown Up Stuff
added.description: Puppycorn doesn't want to grow up. To ease his woes, Unikitty spends the day teaching him all the fun things about being an adult.

added.title: Stop the Presses
added.description: Richard's newspapers aren't selling, so his friends pull out all the stops to put the printed word back on top.

added.title: Castles and Kitties
added.description: Score Creeper traps the gang in a fantasy role playing game where they must follow a complex set of rules to win their freedom.

added.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays Part 1
added.description: Unikitty and the gang secretly throw Master Frown the birthday of his dreams, but their efforts have lasting repercussions beyond Frown's special day.

added.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays Part 2
added.description: Following the events of Master Frown's birthday, Unikitty and her friends form a resistance group to restore the Unikingdom.

added.title: Pool Duel
added.description: Unikitty and the gang are having a great time at the public pool, until they try to get Puppycorn to swim in the deep end with them. Puppycorn is terrified of the deep end. Now Unikitty and the gang must get him over his fear, so he can have maximum pool fun. Meanwhile, Master Frown and Brock are hatching a plan to ruin everyone's fun, by pulling the pool's plug.

added.title: This Spells Disaster
added.description: The gang is planning a surprise for Puppycorn, so they spell things out when talking so he won't find out. Desperate to know what they're saying, Puppycorn finds a magic book that he thinks will help him learn to spell, but unbeknownst to him, it's teaching him how to cast spells! Will Puppycorn realize that knowledge is power and some secrets are kept for a reason?

added.title: Memory Amok
added.description: When Puppycorn witnesses Unikitty do the most embarrassing thing ever, he vows he will never forget it. Desperate, Unikitty uses Dr. Fox's memory machine to erase Puppycorn's memory of the embarrassing event. In the process, Unikitty accidentally releases all of Puppycorn's memories. Now she and the gang must scramble to capture all the scampering memories, or Puppycorn will forget his life.

added.title: No Sleep Sleepover
added.description: It's a sleepover at the castle and Unikitty and Puppycorn want to stay up all night, believing something magical must happen if you stay up long enough.​ At first the friends are game to stay up all night, but as they fall asleep one by one, Unikitty worries they won't make it! How far will she and her bro go to stay awake, and will they discover the secret reason people are supposed to go to bed when the Sandman shows up?

added.title: Kitty & Hawk
added.description: When Puppycorn's favorite toy goes missing, Unikitty & Hawkodile team up to track down the thief, buddy-cop style! But when things get tough and the case goes cold, now it's not just their partnership on the line, but their friendship!

added.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
added.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

added.title: Action Forest
added.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Dos mentiras una verdad
added.description: Cuando Lloyd desenmascara y revela la identidad de Mystake, el Emperador Garmadon acepta a Harumi como su hija de la oscuridad. Mientras tanto, Wu se aferra a su fe al llevar a sus amigos hacia territorios Oni peligrosos esperando encontrar el nido de la Primogénita.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Two Lies, One Truth
added.description: As Lloyd unmasks Mystake for who she truly is, Emperor Garmadon embraces Harumi as his daughter of darkness. Meanwhile, Wu holds onto faith as he leads his friends into dangerous Oni territory in the hope of finding Firstbourne's nest

added.title: The Weakest Link
added.description: Lloyd turns the tables on Harumi to take his father's power away, and the Ninja learn what it takes to be a Dragon Hunter.

added.title: El eslabon mas debil
added.description: Lloyd le paga con la misma moneda a Harumi para quitarle el poder a su padre, y los Ninjas aprenden lo que se necesita para ser un Cazador de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Salvando a Faith
added.description: Lloyd y su equipo planean tomar el control del Oni Titan. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, los Ninja caen en las garras del Barón de Hierro y un viejo maestro regresa.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Saving Faith
added.description: Lloyd and his team plot to take control of the Oni Titan. Meanwhile in the First Realm, the Ninja fall into Iron Baron's clutches and an old master returns.

added.title: Lecciones para un maestro
added.description: Cuando el Barón de Hierro obliga a Wu a tomar la Armadura de Dragón, las cosas no salen como se planearon. En Ninjago, hay un límite de lo que Lloyd puede soportar mientras se aferra a la esperanza del regreso de los Ninjas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Lessons for a Master
added.description: When Iron Baron forces Wu to retrieve the Dragon Armor, things don't go as planned. In Ninjago, Lloyd can only endure so much as he holds onto hope for the Ninjas' return.

added.title: Green Destiny
added.description: The Ninja finally return home and unite to stop Emperor Garmadon, forcing Lloyd to make a decision that will forever change Ninjago.

added.title: Destino verde
added.description: Los Ninjas regresan por fin a casa y se unen para detener al Emperador Garmadon, obligando a Lloyd a tomar una decisión que cambiará por siempre a Ninjago.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Inventor Mentor
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to Italy to help a young girl who wants to be a great inventor.

added.title: Halloween vs. Navidad
added.description: Cuando Santa Claus intenta apoderarse de Halloween, los Titanes necesitan a un par de espíritus para detenerlo.

added.title: Salsa Picante
added.description: La búsqueda de su salsa picante favorita hace que los Osos se involucren en una operación de picadura.

added.title: Public Radio
added.description: After listening to a public radio broadcast during class, Clarence is inspired to record a radio interview of his own featuring his buddy Sumo. When Ms. Baker hears the charming interview, she calls in a favor and gets Clarence a spot on the actual Aberdale Public Radio! The search is on - to find the perfect interview subject for his big day.

added.title: Mama a la Orden
added.description: Con el deseo de tener la experiencia de una madre, los osos usan una aplicación que les traerá una madre a la puerta de sus casas.

added.title: Dinosaur Day
added.description: Pizza Steve's jealousy ruins Uncle Grandpa's Dinosaur Day celebration for Mr. Gus.

added.title: Officer Moody
added.description: Pieces of Mr. Reese's past are revealed when his old partner on the police force, Officer Moody, visits Aberdale Elementary.

added.title: Los Jovenes Titanes Salvan la Navidad
added.description: Santa renuncia a la Navidad, y los Titanes deben intervenir para salvar la festividad.

added.title: Missing Cat
added.description: When Chelsea accidentally lets her pet cat Crumbles out, the cat goes missing! Reluctant to ask for help, she struggles to find the cat before anyone realizes it's gone. It's up to cat whisperer Clarence to interject and find Crumbles, whether Chelsea wants his help or not!

added.title: Dare Day
added.description: With Jeff on vacation, Sumo and Clarence egg each other on in a series of increasingly absurd and extreme dares. But will one of them put a stop to this dare day, before it goes too far?

added.title: A Sumoful Mind
added.description: When Jeff realizes Sumo's new classes have been rubbing off on Sumo, he attempts to further foster this newfound intellectual Sumo! But will Clarence's lowbrow antics reverse Jeff's hard work?

added.title: Peliculas Navidenas
added.description: En Nochebuena, los Osos bebé impiden un robo en una tienda de videos.

added.title: Omnicoptero
added.description: Cuando el ingeniero Phil Billings, amigo del Abuelo Max, le regala al equipo Tennyson el Omni-Copter, un vehículo volador de última generación que puede transportar el Rustbucket hasta aventuras en el extranjero, Vapor Smythe sube a los cielos para obligar a aterrizar el primer vuelo de prueba de Ben y su familia. Pero sin que nuestros héroes lo sepan, Smythe fue enviado a combatir las formas alienígenas más nuevas de Ben por un misterioso y poderoso enemigo: el Caballero por Siempre.

added.title: The Mysterious Boy/A New Power
added.description: The Mysterious Boy: After stopping Tiko's rampage, the Awesome Brawlers have become world-famous heroes and Bakugan-mania sweeps the globe. With the Bakugan boom, brawling has been reinvented as a sporting game. In celebration of the Awesome Brawlers efforts, a tournament is being held in their honor. But the battles are quickly cut short when a rogue brawler and his golden Bakugan crash the event./A New Power: A Rogue brawler, Agit and his golden Bakugan have crashed the Awesome Brawlers party. Who is this brawler? How can he control a Golden Bakugan? Only one way to find out - Bakugan Brawl! Dan and Drago go head to head with the outsides to get to the bottom of it. Outmatched by their opponent, Dan and Drago get a little help from a new powerful weapon - Baku-Gear.

added.title: Esto llega hasta el Once
added.description: Durante una última parada en una juguetería antes del viaje inaugural de Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max a través del Atlántico, Ben se encuentra con su antiguo bravucón, Kevin 11, que ahora tiene nuevos poderes. Es capaz de transformarse en alienígenas al igual que Ben, como el doble "pirata" de Cannonbolt: iWreckingbolt!

added.title: Baku-Gear/Bakugan Rock!
added.description: Baku-Gear: The Awesome Brawlers are excited over their discovery of Baku-Gear, and want to get some footage of it in action. While they're filming, an underclassman named Trey challenges Dan to battle. Who will emerge victorious in the impromptu battle?/Bakugan Rock!: Baku-gear has shown up twice for Dan and Drago and it's starting to eat away at the other awesome brawlers. It's time they take it into their own hands. When Lia and Wynton go up against the rockin' new brawlers in town, they show Dan and Drago that they are not the only one who can summon this cool new tool!

added.title: Convencion de Rath
added.description: De regreso en casa, Ben no puede inscribirse en un concurso de cosplay de gatos sin su propio disfraz. Pero cuando se convierte en Rath, un nuevo alienígena con aspecto felino y mal carácter, el lado salvaje que Ben acaba de descubrir pronto tendrá resultados inesperados.

added.title: Brawler Headhunting/Lightning's Entrance Exam
added.description: Brawler Headhunting: As acting president of Kazami International, Shun is called upon to entertain another new young CEO Luca Schmidt, who's interested in doing business with the Kazami International. But Shun quickly realizes something is up when Luca tries woo him over to his brawling team - the Glanz Five. /Lightning's Entrance Exam: The Awesome Brawlers may be world famous heroes, but that doesn't mean they get out of going to school. They are still regular kids, doing regular kid things. But teachers may have something to say when Lightening decides he wants to join his buddies in the classroom.

added.title: Polos Opuestos
added.description: Un viaje al Polo Sur queda patas arriba cuando el equipo Tennyson aterriza en el Polo Norte. Pero Ben rápidamente descubre a los culpables: iSolar y Polar Twain, unos científicos con poder magnético que quieren chantajear al mundo amenazando con invertir los polos magnéticos de la Tierra!

added.title: Trouble Busters!/French Fry Wars
added.description: Trouble Busters!: Now that the Awesome Brawlers are world famous Bakugan experts, they want to help people solve their Bakugan-related problems. When the world's quietest town is experiencing unexplained noises, the Awseome Brawlers are called in to get to the bottom of it./French Fry Wars: The Awesome Brawlers are arguing over who gets to eat the last french-fry. At first, each member makes a case for why they should to be the one to eat it. But the quarrel quickly escalates into trash talk and revealing secrets about one another. With everyone now upset, things take an unexpected turn.

added.title: No lo digas y Hazlo
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max llegan a un parque nacional nativo americano para conocer los plintos de Ayasha, una antigua formación rocosa parecida a la de Stonehenge. Pero cuando llega el siniestro hechicero Hex, iBen debe luchar contra una bestia que Hex hizo mágicamente con rocas enormes!

added.title: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call/Phantom Thief Ajit
added.description: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call: An archeological discovery is made in Los Volmos. Exploration at the site is cut short, when a master thief and his apprentice attempt to steal the ancient Bakugan artifacts. When the Awesome Brawlers hear the news, they step in to thwart the thieves./Phantom Thief Ajit: An Ancient Bakugon artifact from an archeological discovery is placed in the Los Volmos Museum. The Awesome Brawlers are charged with guarding the artifacts from any further attempts thievery.

added.title: The Prisoner Part 1
added.description: Hot Rod and Soundwave compete over leadership of the group, arguing over how to best defeat the Quintessons.

added.title: The Prisoner Part 2
added.description: The dysfunctional team capture a Sharkticon bailiff and Soundwave's attempts to sabotage Hot Rod's leadership don't go as planned.

added.title: The Scientist Part 1
added.description: In order to heal Soundwave's glitch and find out how to free the Autobots and Decepticons from the Loop, the team hunt down a mysterious Quintesson called The Scientist.

added.title: The Scientist Part 2
added.description: While Hot Rod and Soundwave battle the indestructible Scientist, Perceptor and the rest of the team attempt a mass breakout from the Loop.

added.title: The Alliance Part 1
added.description: Freed from the Loop, Optimus and Megatron still have trouble reconciling so it's up to Hot Rod and Soundwave to unite the divided Cybertronians against the Quintesson invaders.

added.title: The Alliance Part 2
added.description: Autobots and Decepticons unite, launching a massive assault on the Quintesson ship.

added.title: El Arbol Perfecto
added.description: Chloe y Polar conducen hacia el norte para encontrar el árbol de Navidad perfecto. Mientras tanto, Pardo y Panda quedan a cargo de la decoración de la casa de Chloe.

added.title: Deseo de Verano
added.description: Cuando Craig decide dejar una luciérnaga dentro de un frasco, termina interfiriendo con el delicado equilibrio del verano.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Del Otro Lado de la Mesa
added.description: Craig almuerza en el restaurante donde trabaja su hermano mayor y pide un plato de VENGANZA… y muchos palitos de pan.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la autora
added.description: iCraig y Stacks ayudan a Kelsey a convertirse en una verdadera autora al convertir su historia en un libro!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El consejo del Arroyo
added.description: El juego del circulo siembra el caos en el Arroyo, así que Craig forma un consejo para restaurar el orden.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Cadete Destello
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP forman equipo con una heroína intergaláctica llamada Cadete Destello, con la esperanza de salvar al Arroyo de la negatividad.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Bliss Reminisce
added.description: The Girls learn Bliss' backstory from the Professor, Mojo Jojo, and Bliss herself.

added.title: OK A.U.!
added.description: An evil warlock takes our heroes to a strange alternate universe.

added.title: KO's Health Week
added.description: KO spends a week dispensing healthy tips to everyone in the plaza.

added.title: Rad's Alien Sickness
added.description: When our heroes are infected with a virus, Rad stubbornly refuses to back down.

added.title: Dark Plaza
added.description: KO and the heroes of the Plaza fight to save Lakewood Plaza Turbo with everything on the line.

added.title: Classic Rock
added.description: Batman thinks he's helping a homeless old man who is being mugged on the street only to discover that the man is a powerful wizard being chased by demons in disguise. It turns out the wizard is on a mission to save Shazam from the clutches of Black Adam.

added.title: Power Outage
added.description: A ghoul known as Calythos possesses the Parasite in order to drain the Justice League of its powers and use that stolen strength to open a massive volcano.

added.title: Un dia nevado
added.description: Cuando una tormenta de nieve llega a la ciudad, Master Frown trata de arruinar la diversión de todos fingiendo ser un muñeco de nieve mágico. Pero cuando se congela por dentro, Master Frown debe preocuparse menos por arruinar la diversión de todos y más por no convertirse en un témpano malhumorado, imientras se ve obligado a experimentar la alegría de la temporada navideña!

added.title: Drilling Deep
added.description: At school, Aki struggles with the side effects of his newly replicated Drill Man schematics; later, as Mega Man, he learns to control his Fire Powers in thwarting Drill Man's assault on Skyraisers Inc.

added.title: Night of the Bat
added.description: Superman and other Justice League members have to battle Batman when he gets possessed by an evil Djinn, Uthool, who is intent on using the JL power core to blow a crack in Earth.

added.title: Videodrone
added.description: Mega Man must stop Hypno Woman from turning the students and teachers at Silicon Central into her mindless drones.

added.title: Abate and Switch
added.description: When the JLA tries to stop the Brothers Djinn, the ghoulish trio are able to direct spells on our heroes by saying their names forcing them to disguise themselves as each other in order to foil the spells.

added.title: Permanent Retirement
added.description: Grandpa, Gwen and Ben visit an old maid relative only to find that her retirement community has been overtaken by a shapeshifting aliens called Limax.

added.title: Please Rush Home
added.description: A misunderstanding between Mega Man and Rush ends in the robo-pup running away from home, only to be reunited and reconciled during a confrontation with Wave Man.

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Blaze of Glory
added.description: Mega Man and Suna must overcome a sibling dispute over what to do on their day off in order to stop Fire Man from overheating the city.

added.title: Nice on Ice
added.description: An "unscheduled" TV appearance not only lands Aki in hot water for missing class, but sets Ice Man on a misguided mission to "unite" (i.e. freeze together) every human and robot couple in the city!

added.title: Random Acts of Memory
added.description: The Warriors learn that Nohyas has been using a Selective Memory Magisword to erase select interactions with Prohyas' bizarre doppelganger their entire lives, so their new mission: take back that sword!

added.title: Elect to Decline
added.description: Noville wants to impress Vambre with a new Magisword from the Cave of Stuff, but the Cave Weirdos are in election mode and horrible smear campaigning is making Noville's simple task impossible!

added.title: They See Me Trollblin
added.description: The tiny Kotassians hire the Warriors to exterminate two humongous Trollblins that have invaded their village, but it turns out that the Trollblins are actually nice guys and the Warriors switch sides to protect them in a Kotassiam/Trollblin War!

added.title: Hideous Hound
added.description: Prohyas pets an unsightly stray dog, and from that moment on the poor pooch appears on a variety of Warrior missions, driving Vambre and Vambre's brain insane!

added.title: Getting Ahead
added.description: When the headless body of Omnibus knocks at their door, the Warriors use Magiswords to try to make a head they can talk to with mixed results!

added.title: Food Around the Corner
added.description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

added.title: Return to Forever
added.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

added.title: OTTO Motive
added.description: Kevin and Rook run into an old enemy from the Null Void while attending an intergalactic auto show. (Re-introducing classic Ben alien, Upgrade.)

added.title: A Fistful of Brains
added.description: Grandpa Max and Rook are looking all over the galaxy for Ben, who is trapped on Khyber's hidden personal hunting preserve.

added.title: Lista de Traviesos
added.description: Es Nochebuena y Brock está emocionado por la visita de Santa Claus. Mientras se prepara para que Master Frown le lea un cuento para dormir, Unikitty y la banda irrumpen en su casa. Están ahí para evitar que Master Frown arruine más Navidades. Frown se declara inocente, pero Unikitty y la banda cuentan las historias de las Navidades pasadas que ya arruinó. ¿Frown probará su inocencia o se pondrá a la cabeza de la lista de los traviesos?

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Feria de ciencias misteriosas 201x
added.description: K.O. ayuda a Dendy con su proyecto para feria de ciencias.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Mystery Science Fair 201X
added.description: KO helps Dendy with her science fair project.

added.title: Return of Thermometron 9000
added.description: During a brutal heatwave, Axel and his team must track down Thermometron 9000, stolen by Ice Crusher for two purposes - to keep his hockey rink from melting and to bait the good toys into a rematch!

added.title: Just Like Robots
added.description: Axel and the team find themselves bested by Madcap when the baddie uses their digital devices to track their every move in combat, forcing our heroes to act unpredictably.

added.title: Suelta
added.description: Cuando el espíritu de Adorabat trasciende su cuerpo durante un ejercicio de meditación, Mao Mao y Colosal tienen que descubrir un modo de devolverla al mundo real.

added.title: Enfrenta Tus Miedos
added.description: Atrapados en una tienda de mascotas, Manzana y Cebollín deben enfrentarse a sus miedos para poder evitar que Papa Frita se enfrente a los suyos.

added.title: Jefe de Cocina
added.description: Mao Mao se enfrenta a Colosal en una competencia para determinar si cocinar (y ser un héroe) es un arte o una ciencia.

added.title: Sin Cebollin
added.description: Manzana trata de sobrevivir un fin de semana solo mientras cuida la planta de Cebollín.

added.title: Papel de Bano Bebecin
added.description: Manzana necesita conseguir la provisión del papel higiénico que usaría en toda su vida para terminar su escultura de arte moderno.

added.title: El Comienzo de Cobrangutan
added.description: Mao Mao incita a Cobrangután y a los Piratas del Cielo a convertirse en villanos verdaderamente malvados, dignos de un héroe legendario como él.

added.title: Como Robots
added.description: Axel y el equipo se ven superados por Madcap cuando el malo usa sus dispositivos digitales para rastrear cada uno de sus movimientos en combate, lo que obliga a nuestros héroes a actuar de manera impredecible.

added.title: La Captura de Colosal
added.description: Colosal se cansa de sus responsabilidades en el cuartel general de sheriff y decide unirse a los Piratas del Cielo.

added.title: No es Gracioso
added.description: Cuando se acerca el aniversario de seis meses de amistad, Manzana tiene que encontrar una manera de no perder a su mejor amigo.

added.title: Revienta Fiestas
added.description: Los planes de la fiesta de Manzana y Cebollín son interrumpidos por un invitado malhumorado.

added.title: El regreso de Thermometron 9000
added.description: Durante una ola de calor brutal, Axel y su equipo deben rastrear Thermometron 9000, robado por Ice Crusher para dos propósitos: ievitar que su pista de hockey se derrita y cebar los buenos juguetes en una revancha!

added.title: Fiebre de la Baya de Azúcar
added.description: Mao Mao intenta ocultar su amor por el pastel de fruta.

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: Prime Mates/Coupe D'Etat
added.description: Prime Mates: Back when Mojo Jojo tried to take over the world with primates, there was one monkey who didn't get his due: Mopey Popo. Now, Mopey is back to try and be just as evil as Mojo intended./Coupe D'Etat: When the Professor tricks out his car, the girls realize that this K.A.R.R. is taking the Professor away from them both figuratively and literally.

added.title: Makes Zen to Me/Say Uncle
added.description: Makes Zen to Me: When Buttercup gets a fortune cookie saying peace lies within, the most violent of Powerpuffs sets out on a quest for inner peace./Say Uncle: The girls' go to pick up the Professor's brother at the train station, but mistake him for a wild-man being transported to the circus.

added.title: Silent Treatment/Sweet "n" Sour
added.description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

added.title: Artesanias traviesas
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic libera al señor de las travesuras del interior una reliquia antigua, V y V tienen que trabajar en equipo para volver a encerrarlo.

added.title: Futbol a Muerte
added.description: Cuando Vic no elige a Val para su equipo de fútbol, Val promete ganar con su propio equipo. Pero cuando su equipo no está a la altura, recurre a medios sobrenaturales para ganar.

added.title: Quintos Quinces
added.description: Victor y Valentino quieren ir a la fiesta en la piscina de un amigo el mismo día que la fiesta de quince años de su abuela, así que usan una flauta mágica que les permite teletransportarse y asistir a ambas al mismo tiempo.

added.title: La Leyenda del Parque Patinetas
added.description: Mientras buscan un parque de patinaje escondido, V y V se encuentran con una tribu de niños salvajes, que viven en una sociedad sin reglas ni adultos.

added.title: Amor de hermanos
added.description: Después de romper la planta de Chata, Vic y Val deben cumplir con la tarea aparentemente fácil de reemplazarla, lo cual demuestra no serlo cuando sus disputas ponen en peligro Monte Macabro.

added.title: Dia de limpieza
added.description: Victor y Valentino adquieren un nuevo respeto por la limpieza después de que la casa de Chata los atrapa dentro de su laberinto de paredes antiguas y mágicas.

added.title: La ninera
added.description: Vic y Val quieren colarse en un espectáculo secreto de fuegos artificiales, pero su plan se ve frustrado cuando su nueva niñera, Xochi, los supera en todo momento.

added.title: Huracan Chata
added.description: Cuando V y V descubren que las emociones de Chata controlan el agua del lago, deciden sacar ventaja y comienzan su propio negocio de piscinas de olas.

added.title: Loteria
added.description: Cuando Vic hace trampa en un juego de mesa encantado, los malvados personajes cobran vida, y V y V son los responsables de averiguar cómo volver a ponerlos en el juego.

added.title: El club de los solitarios
added.description: En lugar de celebrar el Día de San Valentín, Vic y Val se atreven a explorar una mansión encantada con sus rivales, Charlene y Piña.

added.title: We Are Heroes
added.description: KO struggles with his upgraded role as a member of the hero team.

added.title: TKO Rules!
added.description: KO and TKO decide to swap places for the day.

added.title: K.O. vs Fink
added.description: When Fink taunts KO for being a momma's boy, he grapples with newfound insecurity about it.

added.title: Whatever Happened to... Rippy Roo?
added.description: Rippy Roo visits the plaza.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Big Reveal
added.description: KO finds out who his father is.

added.title: Super Black Friday
added.description: After being forced to work on a holiday, KO, Rad and Enid take a stand.

added.title: RMS & Brandon's First Episode
added.description: A Real Magic Skeleton discovers a new job opportunity.

added.title: OK Dendy
added.description: Dendy fills in for KO at the bodega.

added.title: Action News
added.description: Dynamite Watkins has to go extreme lengths breaking a new story.

added.title: Hope This Flies
added.description: Rad attempts to upgrade his van and make it fly.

added.title: The Past Revealed/Run! A Storm's on the Way
added.description: The Past Revealed: After getting lost in maze with Lia, Ajit remembers the day he met Pharol and Auxilataur. He finally can explain how he was able to partner with golden Bakugan, but Ajit's story is interrupted by a familiar face - Storm!/Run! A Storm's on the Way: Still upset that Ajit has given up his life as a phantom thief, Storm rolls out Hydranoid x Aquos and attacks! Ajit and Lia take off running through the maze as Storm gives chase.

added.title: Golden Bakugan Encounter/Ties of Gold
added.description: Golden Bakugan Encounter: Dan and Shun, split up from the rest of Awesome Brawlers, are traveling in through the maze when they discover McQ. It turns out McQ is seeking a golden Bakugan. When the boys go in for a closer look, they are startled by an old friend, and together confront McQ./Ties of Gold: The now reunited Awesome Brawlers are once again confronted by Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, who are on the hunt for golden Bakugan. With tired Bakugan, the Awesome Brawlers will have to give it their all to defend against this evil.

added.title: Nightmare/Bad Dan
added.description: Nightmare: Dan hasn't been sleeping well lately. No "sleep brawling" this time, but he's constantly tossing and turning. It turns out, Dan's dreams have been hijacked by Haavik, who's trying to spread his vision of chaos and destruction to Dan!/Bad Dan: Haavik has taken control of Dan and sends him on a Bakugan rampage! With "Bad Dan" causing all kinds of havoc and destruction, the rest of the Awesome Brawlers have no choice but to roll out to try to contain "Bad Dan".

added.title: Dusk Industries Under Attack/Taking Dan Back
added.description: Dusk Industries Under Attack: "Bad Dan" has his taken his rampage to Dusk Industries and this time he has help spreading the chaos and destruction, he's joined by Sophie, McQ, Everett, Storm and Haavik! The Awesome Brawlers are quickly on the scene try to bring an end to the show of destruction./ Taking Dan Back: "Bad Dan" with Haavik's crew and their fusion Bakugan continue the rampage at Dusk Industries. The Awesome Brawlers, with some help from Magnus, are determined to an end to this show of destruction and get their friend back!

added.title: Who's the Fake?!/Trouble Busters! 2
added.description: With the reveal that Haavik is a shapeshifting Alien, the ABs start to get super-paranoid, realizing that ANYONE could be Haavik in disguise. The suspicion quickly turns inward, and the ABs are left wondering if they have an imposter among them!/ A kid brawler named Oliver has lost his Bakugan! This seems like a job for the Trouble Busters. The Awesome Brawlers help him chase down and try to catch the elusive Bakugan, who leads them on a wild goose chase through Los Volmos.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Throwing Shade Part 1
added.description: Sgt. Night publicly criticizes Dr. Light's views on human & robot unity during a school assembly, invoking the ire of Fire Man and forcing Silicon City's newly minted hero, Mega Man, to intervene.

added.title: Throwing Shade Part 2
added.description: Mega Man stops Fire Man by replicating his powers and fighting fire with fire. Unfortunately, Mega Man also learns that he can replicate a robot's mental state as well, and must get his own anger under control to win. Defeated, Fire Man reports back to his secret master, Sgt. Night!

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 1
added.description: Lord Obsidian unites the Robot Masters against Mega Man and his family for an epic showdown at the Lighthouse.

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 2
added.description: As Dr. Light and Suna turn the Robot Masters against each other, Mega Man defeats and unmasks his arch nemeses, Lord Obsidian, who turns out to be Sgt. Night in disguise, and finally learns the identity of Namagem, Mega Man's long lost twin brother!

added.title: The Sleeper Part 1
added.description: Despite finding shelter at MacCadam's, Hot Rod is frustrated with their lack of progress rescuing more bots from the Quintesson Loop.

added.title: The Sleeper Part 2
added.description: Hot Rod desperately tries to free Optimus from the Loop while Perceptor and Dead End investigate why MacCadam's is hidden from Quintesson attention.

added.title: The Citizen Part 1
added.description: Hot Rod, Clobber, Dead End, and Whirl search the long-buried Titan for MacCadam and anything to help them defeat the Quintessons.

added.title: The Citizen Part 2
added.description: Joined by Perceptor, the ragtag team discover the dormant Titan is far more dangerous than they expected.

added.title: The Trial Part 1
added.description: To awaken the Titan Iaconus, Hot Rod plans a daring rescue of the Autobot's only City Speaker.

added.title: The Trial Part 2
added.description: The botched rescue leaves Hot Rod captured by the Quintessons, and the rest of the team to deal with a new, unwelcome bot sprung from The Loop.

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Cloris
added.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: The Big Petey Pizza Problem
added.description: Jeff has everything in place for his birthday at Papa Petey's Pins and Pies but Gilben is also having his party there, stealing Jeff's thunder. Jeff gets even more upset when the kids suggest they merge their parities for a double birthday. Can Jeff learn to roll with the punches and share his special day?

added.title: The Break Up
added.description: A silly argument between Jeff and Sumo escalates until they vow never to speak to each other again. At first Clarence enjoys the separation, now he's always got someone to play with but eventually he becomes exhausted and must hatch a scheme to get the guys to be friends again.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: While watching a TV show about dreams, Clarence dozes off and enters the whimsical dreamscape that hovers above Aberdale. Here Clarence can see other people's dreams, experiencing the subconscious of all his friends and neighbors. But when things turn nightmarish, Clarence must find a way to escape back to reality.

added.title: Balance
added.description: Ms. Baker introduces a new student, a short little kid with a hook for a hand named Balance. Clarence is pumped to have a new friend, despite Balance's gruff attitude and snarky jibes at the other kids. When Clarence discovers a disturbing secret about Balance, he and Belson team up to expose him for who he truly is.

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
added.description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

added.title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
added.description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

added.title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
added.description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Cat Man Do/Impeach Fuzz
added.description: Cat Man Do: Bubbles saves a seemingly innocent kitty from the clutches of an evil villain. But when the girls discover it's actually the Cat who is evil, they must save the Professor from being the next victim./Impeach Fuzz: When Fuzzy Lumkins throws his hat into the mayoral ring and claims a surprise victory, it's up to the Mayor and the girls to wrestle the office, and the Mayor's actual hat, back from him.

added.title: Cheep Thrills
added.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: Rainy Day
added.description: The girls get into trouble when left to entertain themselves on a rainy day.

added.title: Electric Buttercup
added.description: Buttercup gets more than she bargained for when she makes a deal with a cool '80s metalhead to get a sweet new guitar.

added.title: Poorbucks
added.description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

added.title: The Incredible Tiny Warriors
added.description: The Warriors must use a Legendary Magisword to defeat a giant king who wants to eat celebrities. This proves difficult when being eaten by the King makes Vambre feel very small.

added.title: Helping Cattus Help
added.description: The search for a mythical creature gets rather metaphysical when the equally elusive Cattus' assists the mission.

added.title: Warts and All
added.description: Witchy Simone accidentally turns Vambre into a frog and Prohyas and Witchy try to change her back.

added.title: Too Commercial
added.description: The Warriors go advertising crazy; Grup tries to stop them for their own good!

added.title: The Cave of Gelatinous Doom!
added.description: The Warriors don't have a worthy adventure to use their impressive new skull-and-crossbones-emblazoned Bonehead Magisword until they are sent on a quest to battle a mighty slime beast in the Dungeon of Gelatinous Doom!

added.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get distracted while setting up chairs for a kids birthday party and unleash a monster that terrorizes the entire park.

added.title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
added.description: In order to impress Margret and ask her out, Mordecai hangs with a bunch of punk Unicorns who say they can help him get his lady.

added.title: Don
added.description: Rigby's estranged accountant brother comes back to help save the park from an audit. While everyone loves Don, Rigby wants nothing to do with him.

added.title: Rigby's Body
added.description: After Rigby eats an excessive amount of junk food, his body quits on him, leaving him a ghost-like consciousness. Mordecai and Skips must find his body before the day is over.

added.title: Washington B.C.
added.description: Ben must use the Omnitrix to transform into alien heroes to battle Dr. Amino and his transmorphed dinosaurs running rampant in Washington DC.

added.title: The Krakken
added.description: While stopped at a lakefront campsite, Ben has a chance encounter with a Loch Ness type sea monster called a Krakken, controlled by an evil poacher.

added.title: Many Happy Returns
added.description: Gwen and Kevin pay Ben a surprise visit, but does Kevin's strange behavior have anything to do with an angry Tetramand princess, or her father's fleet of warships prepared to attack the Earth?

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Mr. Smoothy's
added.description: The Plumbers' resident geniuses, Blukic and Driba set off to find some smoothies meanwhile Ben and Rook try to stop Trombipulor from gaining the source of absolute power.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: Showdown Part 2
added.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 1
added.description: The Incursean Armada, with the help of Dr. Psychobos, have invaded the Earth. (Reintroducing old Ben alien, BenMummy.)

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: Evil's Encore
added.description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

added.title: Follow that Space Cab!
added.description: While Superman escorts his prisoner Mr. Mind between planets, he is attacked by Lobo who wants to collect a reward on Mind. Temporarily powered-down, Superman seeks Space Cabbie's help to get away from Lobo.

added.title: El Silencio
added.description: ¿Acaso Gumball y Darwin se quedaron sin cosas que decirse el uno al otro?
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Deseo
added.description: Gumball y Darwin creen que convirtieron a la señorita Simian en un almohadón para el cuello.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Agente
added.description: En una misión escolar super secreta, Gumball se comporta como cierto sofisticado agente secreto británico.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Desastre
added.description: Gumball y Darwin cuidan y luego pierden a la hermanita de Penny.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Los Mejores Amigos
added.description: Cuando el mejor amigo de Gumball regresa a la ciudad, Darwin se pone celoso.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Revuelta
added.description: Darwin siente pena por los objetos del hogar en Elmore y los motiva a alzarse.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Que Tal Este Especial? Espacio: 1º. Parte
